This list serves as a reference architecture. It reflects what senior backend and solution architects use when designing enterprise-grade eCommerce platforms (e.g., Amazon, Myntra, Nike).

1. Core Foundational Services

1.1 User & Identity Service
- User registration and authentication (email, phone, social logins)
- Password reset, email verification
- Role-based access (admin, customer, vendor)
- Profile management (name, DOB, gender, avatar)
- Session & token lifecycle management (JWT, Firebase, OAuth2)
- Account deactivation, GDPR compliance (data deletion/export)

1.2 Product Catalog Service
- Product master table (name, description, brand, category, tags)
- Product variants (size, color, SKU)
- Product pricing, currency conversion
- Product availability & visibility rules
- SEO metadata, product URLs
- Product media (images, videos)
- Category hierarchy, collections
- Brand, material, season metadata

1.3 Inventory Service
- SKU-level stock tracking
- Multi-warehouse or location-based inventory
- Stock reservation & release during checkout
- Real-time stock updates (low-stock alerts, out-of-stock handling)

1.4 Cart Service
- Add/update/remove items
- Guest carts (temporary) vs. user carts (persistent)
- Merge logic after login
- Quantity validation (against stock)
- Price recalculation (for dynamic pricing)
- Promotions/discount preview in cart

1.5 Wishlist Service
- Add/remove products from wishlist
- Guest vs. authenticated wishlist
- Merge on login
- Multi-list support (favorites, gifts)
- Share wishlist (public link, email, social)
- Sync across devices

2. Transaction & Order Services

2.1 Checkout Service
- Address selection
- Payment selection (COD, online)
- Price breakdown (subtotal, tax, shipping, discount)
- Validation of stock and pricing
- Order summary confirmation step

2.2 Payment Gateway Service
- Integration with providers (Stripe, Razorpay, PayPal)
- Transaction records, refunds, status callbacks
- Payment retries & expiration handling
- Secure tokenized storage (PCI DSS compliance)
- Reconciliation logs

2.3 Order Management Service
- Order creation, confirmation, cancellation, returns
- Order line items linked to products & pricing
- Order status tracking (placed, shipped, delivered)
- Order history, invoice generation
- Refund workflow (partial/full)
- Communication triggers (emails, SMS, push notifications)

3. Customer Services

3.1 Address Book Service
- Add/update/delete addresses
- Default billing & shipping address
- Pincode validation, address autocomplete
- Internationalization (country/state formats)

3.2 Reviews & Ratings Service
- Product reviews (verified purchase flag)
- Ratings breakdown (1–5 stars)
- Moderation & spam detection
- Review replies (for brand engagement)

3.3 Loyalty & Rewards Service
- Reward points system (earn, redeem)
- Tier levels (silver, gold, platinum)
- Birthday/anniversary perks
- Referral program tracking

3.4 Notifications Service
- Email notifications (order updates, promotions)
- Push notifications (mobile/web)
- In-app notification center
- SMS gateway integration
- Preference management (opt-in/out)

4. Logistics & Fulfillment Services

4.1 Shipping Service
- Integration with carriers (Shiprocket, FedEx, UPS)
- Shipping methods (standard, express)
- Tracking number assignment
- Real-time status updates
- Estimated delivery calculation

4.2 Returns (RMA) Service
- Return/replace requests
- Refund or store credit issuance
- Reverse logistics tracking
- Approval workflows

4.3 Warehouse Management Service
- Stock intake and dispatch
- Bin-level tracking
- Barcode/QR management
- Inventory reconciliation reports

5. Marketing & Discovery Services

5.1 Search & Discovery Service
- Full-text search with filters
- Search suggestions, autocomplete
- Sorting (price, popularity, rating)
- Personalized recommendations
- AI-powered product similarity search

5.2 Promotions & Discounts Service
- Coupon codes, promo rules
- Category/brand-specific discounts
- First-order discounts
- Bundled offers, “buy X get Y”
- Cart-level promotions

5.3 Analytics & Tracking Service
- Product view tracking
- Conversion funnels
- Cart abandonment analytics
- Heatmaps & click tracking

5.4 CMS (Content Management System)
- Home banners, landing pages
- Blog/news updates
- Custom pages for marketing campaigns
- Static content management (FAQs, T&Cs)

6. Administrative & Support Services

6.1 Admin Dashboard Service
- Manage products, users, orders, promotions
- Role-based permissions (admin, moderator)
- Real-time metrics (sales, users, stock)
- Support tools (refunds, order edits)

6.2 Customer Support Service
- Ticket system (issue tracking)
- Live chat integration
- FAQ automation (chatbot-ready)
- Escalation handling

6.3 Audit & Logging Service
- Record all key user/admin actions
- Error logs, access logs
- Security audit trails
- Integration with monitoring (Elastic, Datadog)

7. Technical & Cross-Cutting Services

7.1 Authentication Gateway
- Centralized user token validation
- API key management for microservices
- Session management (HTTP-only cookies, refresh tokens)

7.2 Database & Cache Layer
- PostgreSQL/MySQL for relational data
- Redis for session & caching
- Elasticsearch for product search
- CDN for image delivery

7.3 File/Media Service
- Upload and serve product images/videos
- Compression, thumbnailing
- Cloud storage (AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage)

7.4 Configuration & Feature Flag Service
- Manage runtime flags for experiments (A/B testing)
- Toggle features safely in production

7.5 Security Service
- Rate limiting, IP blocking
- CSRF/XSS protection
- CAPTCHA integration
- Token revocation and refresh
- CORS policy enforcement

8. Advanced / Enterprise-Level Extensions

8.1 Recommendation Engine
- Collaborative filtering
- Personalized home feed
- Recently viewed, trending now

8.2 Subscription Service
- Product subscriptions (monthly refills)
- Subscription billing and renewal logic
- Auto-shipping and payment retry

8.3 Multi-Vendor Marketplace Service
- Seller onboarding
- Product approval workflow
- Commission tracking
- Vendor dashboards

8.4 Fraud Detection & Risk Management
- Transaction anomaly detection
- Device fingerprinting
- Suspicious behavior alerts

8.5 Internationalization Service
- Multi-currency pricing
- Regional catalogs
- Language localization (i18n, l10n)
- Taxation rules per country

Summary: Typical Domain/Service Layer Breakdown
Layer                Example Services
User & Identity       Users, Auth, Profile, Sessions
Product Catalog       Products, Variants, Media, Categories
Sales                 Cart, Wishlist, Checkout, Orders, Payments
Customer              Addresses, Reviews, Loyalty, Notifications
Logistics             Shipping, Returns, Warehouse
Marketing             Promotions, Search, CMS, Analytics
Admin                 Dashboard, Support, Audit Logs
Infrastructure        Auth Gateway, DB, Cache, File, Security
